    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of Aug 19 article about Fresh Air Fund's Camp Tommy, which referred incorrectly in some copies to timing of $2.8 million in donations by fund's namesake, fashion designer Tommy Hilfiger</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Because of an editing error, an article on Aug. 19 about the Fresh Air Fund's Camp Tommy referred incorrectly in some copies to the timing of $2.8 million in donations to the fund by its namesake, the fashion designer Tommy Hilfiger. He donated $1 million from his foundation in 1999 and $1.8 million in July from a celebrity golf tournament that he organized. The total was not all donated in July.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Because of an editing error, an article on Aug. 19 about the Fresh Air Fund's Camp Tommy referred incorrectly in some copies to the timing of $2.8 million in donations to the fund by its namesake, the fashion designer Tommy Hilfiger. He donated $1 million from his foundation in 1999 and $1.8 million in July from a celebrity golf tournament that he organized. The total was not all donated in July.</p>
      </block>
